[12:53:11] {"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/.coda/skills/generating-test-cases/references/phase-a-epic-func-suites.md", "content": "1: # Phase A: Per-Epic Functional Test Suite Generation -- Atomic Loop\n2: \n3: ## Context Contract\n4: - **Inputs:** FTC_INDEX (scoped_epics, suite_status), FTC_CONTEXT (stories_by_epic, tool_selections, mvp_epics, prd_business_rules), Upstream Rules (from SKILL.md Step 4)\n5: - **Outputs:** One file per epic in SUITES_SUBFOLDER/epic-{NN}-func-tests.md\n6: - **Carries Forward:** FTC_INDEX.epic_suites, .tc_catalog, .ac_coverage, .business_rule_coverage per epic\n7: - **Flush After:** Each epic's test case text flushed BEFORE the next\n8: - **H1 Title per file:** `# {project_name} -- EPIC-XX: {Title} Functional Tests`\n9: \n10: ## Output Quality Protocols\n11: - **AC Exhaustion:** Every acceptance criterion -> at least one Then assertion.\n12: - **Business Rule Coverage:** Every business rule -> at least one scenario.\n13: - **Anti-Truncation:** Full Gherkin for ALL test cases. No skipping.\n14: - **Uniform Depth:** Last story's TCs = same depth as first story's.\n15: - **Risk-Based Depth:** MVP epics get extra negative/boundary scenarios.\n16: \n17: ## Mode-Specific Behavior\n18: - **REPAIR:** Check if REPAIR_DIRECTIVES target this epic.\n19:   IF none -> SKIP. IF targeted -> load file, apply, rewrite in place.\n20: - **BUILD:** Generate from scratch.\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ## Atomic Loop Protocol\n25: \n26: **Per-epic with chunked per-story generation inside each epic.**\n27: \n28: ```\n29: REMAINING_EPICS = [epics with PENDING in FTC_INDEX.suite_status]\n30: COMPLETED_EPICS = []\n31: TOTAL_EPICS = len(REMAINING_EPICS)\n32: \n33: WHILE REMAINING_EPICS is not empty:\n34: \n35:   EPIC-XX = REMAINING_EPICS.pop_first()\n36: \n37:   #================================================================\n38:   # PHASE 1: LOAD EPIC SOURCE DATA\n39:   #================================================================\n40: \n41:   1. LOAD stories for this epic from FTC_CONTEXT.stories_by_epic[EPIC-XX]\n42:      For each story: story_id, title, tag, narrative, acceptance_criteria,\n43:      business_rules, in_scope, out_of_scope, dependencies, assumptions.\n44:   2. DETERMINE if MVP epic: EPIC-XX in FTC_CONTEXT.mvp_epics?\n45:      MVP -> full depth (positive + ALL negative + boundary).\n46:      Non-MVP -> positive + key negative only.\n47:   3. LOAD cross-reference business rules from FTC_CONTEXT.prd_business_rules (if available)\n48:   4. IF REPAIR and no directive targets this epic -> SKIP. CONTINUE.\n49: \n50:   ## ZERO INVENTION CHECKPOINT:\n51:   Test cases MUST derive from loaded ACs and business rules.\n52:   No invented business logic. Boundary values from explicit constraints\n53:   or marked [Assumption].\n54: \n55:   #================================================================\n56:   # PHASE 2: CHUNKED PER-STORY GENERATION\n57:   #================================================================\n58: \n59:   STORIES = FTC_CONTEXT.stories_by_epic[EPIC-XX]\n60:   TOTAL_STORIES = len(STORIES)\n61:   CHUNK_SIZE = 2  # stories per chunk (each story produces 3-10+ TCs)\n62:   CHUNKS = split STORIES into groups of CHUNK_SIZE\n63:   TC_COUNTER = 0\n64:   EPIC_FILE = SUITES_SUBFOLDER/epic-{NN}-func-tests.md\n65: \n66:   ## Write File Header\n67:   CREATE FILE at EPIC_FILE with:\n68:     # {project_name} -- EPIC-XX: {Epic Title} Functional Tests\n69:     Priority: {tier} | MVP: {Yes/No} | Stories: {TOTAL_STORIES}\n70:     ---\n71: \n72:   FOR EACH chunk in CHUNKS:\n73: \n74:     chunk_stories = current chunk (up to CHUNK_SIZE stories)\n75: \n76:     FOR EACH story in chunk_stories:\n77: \n78:       ### Analyze Story\n79:       1. Count ACs: {N} acceptance criteria\n80:       2. Count business rules: {N} rules"}}
[12:53:11] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "view", "args": {"file_path": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/.coda/skills/generating-test-cases/references/func-test-cases-template.md", "limit": 80}}
[12:53:11] {"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/.coda/skills/generating-test-cases/references/func-test-cases-template.md", "content": "1: # Agent-Native Functional Test Cases — Template Reference\n2: \n3: ## Architecture: Manifest + Per-Epic Gherkin Suites\n4: \n5: The output is ALWAYS a manifest plus per-epic suite files.\n6: Per-epic files use strict Gherkin format — they are already agent-native\n7: and require no structural changes from v2.0.1.\n8: \n9: ```\n10: FTC/\n11: ├── FTC-MANIFEST-{SESSION_ID}.md   ← Coverage data + validations (always in context)\n12: ├── suites/\n13: │   ├── epic-01-func-tests.md       ← Gherkin test cases (loaded on demand)\n14: │   ├── epic-02-func-tests.md\n15: │   └── ...\n16: └── FTC-AUDIT-{SESSION_ID}.md       ← Session metadata\n17: ```\n18: \n19: **Consumption pattern:**\n20: The QA automation agent loads the MANIFEST (always) + ONE suite file (current work).\n21: When it finishes an epic, it drops the file and loads the next.\n22: It never needs all test cases in context.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## File 1: FTC-MANIFEST-{SESSION_ID}.md\n27: \n28: ```markdown\n29: # {project_name} — Functional Test Cases Manifest\n30: version: {NEW_VERSION}\n31: session: {SESSION_ID}\n32: mode: {BUILD | REPAIR}\n33: date: {ISO 8601}\n34: language: {DETECTED_LANGUAGE}\n35: status: {draft | complete}\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## scope\n40: \n41: - target: {target_epic | \"All Epics\"}\n42: - total_epics: {N}\n43: - total_stories: {N}\n44: - total_test_cases: {N}\n45: - strategy_source: {test_strategy_path}\n46: - mtp_source: {master_test_plan_path}\n47: - stories_source: {user_stories_path}\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## epic_map\n52: \n53: | epic | title | stories | tcs | positive | negative | boundary | mvp | file | status |\n54: |------|-------|---------|-----|----------|----------|----------|-----|------|--------|\n55: | EPIC-01 | {title} | {N} | {N} | {N} | {N} | {N} | Yes | suites/epic-01-func-tests.md | complete |\n56: | EPIC-02 | {title} | {N} | {N} | {N} | {N} | {N} | No | suites/epic-02-func-tests.md | complete |\n57: | EPIC-03 | {title} | {N} | {N} | {N} | {N} | {N} | Yes | suites/epic-03-func-tests.md | pending |\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## tc_catalog\n62: \n63: ### EPIC-01: {title}\n64: \n65: | tc_id | story_id | title | type | tag | priority | ac_or_rule |\n66: |-------|----------|-------|------|-----|----------|------------|\n67: | FTC_01_01_01 | US-01-01-BE | {title} | positive | BE | P0 | AC-01 |\n68: | FTC_01_01_02 | US-01-01-BE | {title} | negative | BE | P0 | AC-02 |\n69: | FTC_01_01_03 | US-01-01-BE | {title} | boundary | BE | P1 | BR-01 |\n70: \n71: ### EPIC-02: {title}\n72: \n73: | tc_id | story_id | title | type | tag | priority | ac_or_rule |\n74: |-------|----------|-------|------|-----|----------|------------|\n75: | FTC_02_01_01 | US-02-01-FE | {title} | positive | FE | P1 | AC-01 |\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## ac_coverage\n80: "}}
